cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.SE, cs.FM 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new temporal logic and proves its first-order completeness. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper deals with model checking procedural programs and introduces a logic based on Operator Precedence Languages. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses temporal logics for reasoning on context-free structures. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper provides a model checking procedure for the introduced logic, which is important in software engineering. 
- cs.FM (Formal Methods) is also relevant as the paper deals with formal verification of programs using temporal logics.
